<br>
They dressed Nefertiri into some newly and specially made shaman leathers, placed a Snow Leopard amulet around her neck and braided back her hair. From there she was taken to the center of the village, where she was layed down on a table. Yakut placed Nefey into a deep trance while two Amazons branded the mark of the Shaman onto Nefertiri's chest just above her heart. All shamaness's had their marks placed there to signify that Shamanism was in their heart and that Shamanism was not an art, but a way of life.<br>
<br>
From there, Nefertiri was awoken and led to a platform. And as in Tradition, she was stripped down and covered in mud. The Mud symbolized earth, and she was naked to show Sister Moon the fullness of her form.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tonight we initiate, our new sister and Shamaness, Nefertiri, into our Tribe. let us fill you with visions from our history, fragments from a time before we were Amazons, when cannibals slaughtered our men and warriors like the great Samsara called on the shaman for a savior from the future - an atman - the first Cyane.&quot;<br>
<br>
Yakut raised an arm to the sky and a vision played out before everyone's eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Behold the Legendary Warrior, Samsara.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Amazons see Samsara asking the shaman to bring forth a Savoir, an Atmah. One appears, its a woman from the future. <br>
<br>
&quot;Her name was Cyane, Her strange ways and clothes confused the tribe. But her courage was real.&quot;<br>
<br>
They see her running with the Tretmolecs, mounting a horse and being praised for her courage. She was the first of the Tretmolecs to ride horses rather than eat them.<br>
<br>
&quot;Tonight your initiation continues a ritual passed down to us through the ages - a ritual of music and movement, a celebration of community and joy, for we are a family united in sisterhood.&quot;<br>
<br>
The Tribal Dancers began their movement and song, while Yakut takes a dagger from her Gaurd and sliced Nefertiri's palm. She drained some of the blood into a silver chalice which held wyne. <br>
<br>
&quot;We are the creators and our own creations - the words and the music - both singer and song. Our traditions stretch back to the great Gaia herself, mother of us all. A tradition of dance … of music … of sacrifice … of blood.&quot;<br>
<br>
And as in tradition, Nefertiri had to howl to the moon til Sister Sun chased away Sister Moon.<br>
<br>
It was finished.<br>
<br>
